	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Former estate agent Vicki Momberg, who was convicted in connection with a racist rant, is expected to appeal her conviction and sentence at the South Gauteng High Court on Monday. She was sentenced in March to three years in prison, of which one year was suspended, following her racist tirade in 2016. Momberg was found guilty of four counts of crimen injuria on November 3 for calling a black police officer the k-word 48 times when he came to her aid following a smash-and-grab incident. READ: Vicki Momberg granted bail, pending her appeal She was released on R2 000 bail by the Randburg Magistrate's Court in August, pending the outcome of her appeal. State prosecutor Yusuf Baba decided not to oppose bail following a discussion with Momberg's lawyer Kingdom Onah. No bail conditions were set. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  